busybox.exe — embedded GNU coreutils for the Windows bash backend
================================================================

This directory ships a prebuilt `busybox.exe` (BusyBox for Windows /
busybox-w32, v1.38.0), v1.38.0-FRP, a single self-contained native Win32 executable. The
daemon embeds it (//go:embed, Windows builds only) and extracts it at runtime to
supply the standard Unix tools — sed, awk, grep, sort, cut, tr, wc, xargs, find,
date, sleep, head, tail, cat, ls, … — that the agent's shell pipelines need on a
Windows host that has no real bash / GNU coreutils. On Linux and macOS nothing is
embedded; the host's native bash and coreutils are used.

